args: It's all your fault that my mom...
I'm sorry. I had no choice.
Damn it! Them Empire chumps\nbrought a huge fiend with 'em!
If we don't stop it right now,\nthe village will be wiped out!
Your Highness, wait!\nDon't run off by yourself!
It almost feels like the fiends\nare getting stronger lately...
I wonder if this has to do with Morsayati\nbeing fully revived now?
Damn! I didn't want the villagers\nto get caught up in this!
But we have to take this fiend out now!
My mom suffered, and it's all your fault!
You should never have come here!
The woman from earlier is conscious\nagain, {player_name}! Hurry!
I'm so glad she's okay! But even so,\nthat doesn't change the fact I put\nall of these people in danger...
You look quite low, Your Highness.
Yeah, keep that chin up! You're just out\nhere doing the best you can, remember?
Boss? This is gonna sound harsh,\nbut if ya let this kinda thing get to ya,\nya ain't gonna be no good to anybody.

This war's gettin' fiercer by the day,
which means folks are gonna be hurt.
There just ain't no way everyone walks
outta this thing with a happy ending.
Still, it's probably not good to have the\npeople we're tryin' to protect angry at us.
You know, King Alberius himself once\nwent through a similar experience.
He fought off the Dyrenell Empire to\nprotect a village. Sadly, the casualties\nfrom that battle were most severe.

Had the king and his allies never come,
the damage would have been lessenedâ€”
or so went the line of reasoning among
people who held him responsible.
What did Alberius do about it?
He simply said, ï¼‚This is the fate that\nawaits all who bear great power.ï¼‚
Yes. And he didn't make any changes to his\npolicies or plans. However...
Let us just say His Majesty was not\nthe type to display his pain openly.
So he buried it inside himself instead?
Alberius was stronger than I knew...
(But I find that strength to be so very...\nlonely. Does that mean I'm weak?)
